'''Tom Faulkner''' (born and died in the 18th century), known as "Long Tom", was a noted English  of the mid-Georgian period.  A  man, he was a prominent single wicket player who frequently played in challenge matches at the .  
He played regularly for the prestigious  in Surrey and appears in the records from 1744 until 1761.  He was also a well-known  under his "Long Tom" sobriquet.  Unfortunately, very little is known of his personal details <ref name=LLB>[http://www.jl.sl.btinternet.co.uk/stampsite/cricket/ladstolords/biog.html#faulkner From Lads to Lord's &ndash; biography of Tom Faulkner]</ref>.